HEADWORD: Cony-catch
<hw>Co"ny-catch</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To deceive; to
cheat; to trick.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Take heed, Signor Baptista, lest you be <qex>cony-catched</qex> in
the this business.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cony-catcher</ent>⟦br⟧
